      "message": "When a display name contains non-ASCII characters AND characters forbidden in a display-name, String() currently return is invalid (issue #11292).\n\nRFC 2047 in section 5.3 forbid the use of characters like double quotes in a display-name.\nAnd our current implementation of Q-encoding does not encode these characters. See the isAllowedInPhrase function for the complete list of additional characters that need to be encoded.\n\nI see 3 ways to fix that issue:\n\n1. Add mime.QPhraseEncoding that is like mime.QEncoding but also encodes the characters forbidden in a display-name and use it in Address.String().\n2. Use base64 encoding (which encodes characters like double quotes): that is what my PR currently does.\n3. Update mime.QEncoding to always encode the additional characters.\n\nI choose 2 because that is what Gmail does.\n3 looks fine too. The only thing is that fields like Subject, will be slightly longer and more unreadable (in the Q-encoded form) since more characters will be encoded.",
